1917-2008 Daniel Anthony Leonesio, a resident of Floresville, Texas, entered into eternal rest on Tuesday, Oct. 14, 2008, at 8:35 a.m., in the Floresville Nursing Center in Floresville at the age of 91 years, 2 months, and 14 days. He was born on July 31, 1917, in Reno, Nev., to Frank H. and Blanche E. Rodgers Leonesio. He graduated from […]

1961-2008 Angie Hernandez Alvizo, a longtime resident of Poth, Texas, passed away on Monday, Oct. 13, 2008, at 12:21 a.m., in the Connally Memorial Medical Center in Floresville, at the age of 46 years, 11 months, and 21 days. She was born to Christina (Herrera) and Miguel Hernandez Sr. on Oct. 22, 1961, in Karnes City. She graduated from Thomas […]

1963-2008 Loretta Ann Riojas passed away Thursday, Oct. 16, 2008, in Floresville, Texas, at the age of 44 years, 11 months, and 14 days. She was born Nov. 2, 1963, in Floresville to Emilio S. and Carmen Garza Quintanilla. She lived in Floresville all her life. Her grandparents preceded her in death. Loretta is survived by her husband, Oscar Riojas […]

1971-2008 Brian Keith Sheppard passed away on Friday, Oct. 17, 2008, at the age of 36 years, from complications from type I diabetes. Brian was born Dec. 19, 1971, in San Antonio, Texas, to James Allen and Suzanne Moczygemba Sheppard. He was preceded in death by his father. He is survived by his mother, Suzanne Sheppard; a daughter, Jordan Haley […]

1947-2008 Jean Ann Muenchow Henkes, beloved wife, mother, grandmother, sister, aunt, and friend, passed away Sunday, Oct. 12, 2008, at the age of 60 with her loving family by her side. She was born Nov. 15, 1947, in St. Hedwig, Texas. Jean was employed by Wells Fargo bank for many years. Being together with her family was her true passion, […]

1916-2008 Thomas Mayfield Ruckman, 91, of Karnes City, Texas, passed away on Saturday, Oct. 11, 2008. Born on the Ruckman Ranch in DeWitt County in November 1916, he is survived by three daughters, Jeanne Conrad and husband Kenneth of Homosassa, Fla., Jan Johnson and husband Colin of Karnes City, and Mary Kass and husband Terry of Arizona; as well as […]

1926-2008 Joe Gonzales Aleman, 82, of Victoria, Texas, died in his home in Victoria Thursday, Oct. 16, 2008. He was born in DeWitt County on July 17, 1926. He retired from Union Carbide after 35 years of service and was a member of Our Lady of Sorrows Catholic Church in Victoria. Joe was preceded in death by his wife, Petra […]

Members of the South Texas Trail Riders will participate in the Harvey J. Tinnell Memorial Play Day Trail Ride Friday through Sunday, Oct. 24-26, at the Refugio Fairgrounds in Refugio. Brittany Wescott of Floresville serves as the 2008-09 South Texas Trail Riders’ queen, with Jessica Brown of Mathis selected as sweetheart. Cassidy Gain of Corpus Christi is this year’s mascot. […]

STOCKDALE — The Guadalupe Valley Family Violence Shelter will host the first-ever “Race Away from Violence” benefit barrel race Saturday, Oct. 25, in the Stockdale Rodeo Arena.
